<span id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p1"></span> <span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p1.1"></span>Canon XL.  (Greek xliii.)</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p2"></span>Concerning the non-frequenting of
taverns by the clergy, except when travelling.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p3"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p3.1"></span>That</span> the clergy are not to enter
taverns for eating or drinking, nor unless compelled to do so by the
necessity of their journey.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p4"></span><span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p4.1"></span>Notes.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p5"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p5.1"></span>Ancient Epitome of Canon XL.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p6"></span>A cleric on a journey may enter a
tavern, otherwise not.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p7"></span>This canon is Canon xxvj. of the Synod
of Hippo, <span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.xli-p7.1"></span>a.d.</span> 393.

